														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4398406">
									

<p>Hollow Knight - Metroidvania, very hard, you're a bug. Fantastic art style. Story is good, but Dark Souls like in the sense that you need an in-depth lore video to get what's going on, which I like.</p>
<p>Shovel Knight - Megaman-Metroid with amazing pixelart and charming story. You're a knight wearing a shovel. Bundle comes with two separate additional campaigns where you play as two of the bosses.</p>
<p>Subnautica - Survival game, it's actually finished and it has a begin-middle-ending story, and a good one at that. You're in the future, stranded on an ocean planet, meaning the devs have complete creative freedom. Surprisingly, this lack of knowledge about what creatures you can encounter makes it surprisingly effective horror at times.</p>

							</div>

								
